Willie Charles HILL v. J. C. TAYLOR, Warden. No. 7149. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Jan. 9, 1963. Thomas W. Inman, Denver, Colo., for petitioner. Newell A. George, U. S. Atty., and Benjamin E. Franklin, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for respondent.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and PICKETT and LEWIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of respondent January 9, 1963, on ground appeal is moot
